    <stitle>NEWAY AD-123/246 DRIVE AXLE AIR SUSPENSIONS - REPLACE - HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</title>
        <para>The height control valve when installed properly on a single valve system will have the punch mark (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0301012">Figure 12</hotlnk>) on the valve spool positioned toward the vertical linkage as
            shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0301012">Figure 12</hotlnk>. If the punch mark is not positioned as shown in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0301012">Figure 12</hotlnk>, the valve will operate in reverse. The punch mark may be hard
            to see because it will be under the lever arm.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0301012" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0301012" filename="../figg03/g0301012.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Height Control Valve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.LEVER ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>2.VERTICAL LINKAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>3.PUNCH MARK</callout1>
                <callout1>4.VALVE SPOOL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
